headline: PayPal (NASDAQ:PYPL) Exceeds Q3 Expectations, Stock Jumps 14.7%
summary: Digital payments platform PayPal (NASDAQ:PYPL) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 7.3% year on year to $8.42 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.34 per share was 11.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
